      "question": "During an FSDP forward pass, why is an all-gather needed before computing a layer?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "Because each GPU has only a shard of that layer's parameters, so the full layer parameters must be temporarily reconstructed for computation.",
